data.title: Jared Leto rocks an all-black look while hitting the red carpet at the 2024 iHeartRadio Music Awards in Los Angeles
data.meta_description: Jared Leto rocked an all-black dapper look while hitting the red carpet at the 2024 iHeartRadio Music Awards.
data.text:
Jared Leto rocked an all-black dapper look while hitting the red carpet at the 2024 iHeartRadio Music Awards.

The 52-year-old singer and actor hit the red carpet solo at the event, held at the Dolby Theatre in Los Angeles on Monday.

The outing comes just weeks after he shared a shirtless video from Argentina following a performance in the South American country.

Leto is set to present at the ceremony, though he isn't up for any awards at the ceremony, hosted by Ludacris.

The actor and singer stepped out wearing a lacy black sequined shirt under a black suit coat for the occasion.

He also opted for a black coat with a unique silver brooch pinned to the lapel for the outing.

Leto completed his look with matching black pants and black shoes as he hit the red carpet.

Just days earlier, Leto was performing in Brazil with his rock group Thirty Seconds to Mars.

The group performed at the 2024 Tecate Pal'Norte Festival at Parque Fundidor in Monterrey, Mexico over the weekend.

The performances are all part of the group's Seasons Tour, their first venture on the road in five years.

The tour kicked off in mid-March in Santiago, Chile, followed by stops in Buenos Aires, Argentina, Asuncion, Paraguay, Bogota, Colombia and Sao Paolo, Brazil.

The group will take all of April off before embarking on the European leg of the tour, which kicks off May 9 in Krakow, Poland.

This leg will go through Germany, Austria, France, Switzerland, Italy, Spain, England and more before wrapping up in mid-June.

After another month hiatus from the road, the group will return for its North American leg starting in Auburn, Washington on July 26.

The group will be performing in a number of outdoor venues like the iconic Red Rocks Amphitheater in Colorado in July and August.

They will also perform in arenas like Barclays Center in Brooklyn throughout this leg that runs through early September.

The tour wraps up with performances in Australia and New Zealand, with final stops in Denmark, Sweden and Norway in early October.
